Rochester.House at 235-237 Reynolds Street: The House at 235-237 Reynolds Street is a historic home located at Rochester in Monroe County, New York. It was constructed between 1880 and 1885 as a multi-family dwelling and is an unusual example of High Victorian Gothic style residential architecture in Rochester's Eighth Ward. It is a modestly sized two-bay, two-story brick structure that features asymmetrical massing and verticality and elongation of architectural elements.
